    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-07-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-10-01T20:02:06Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Intelligent Vehicle Highway Safety Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a deduction from gross income for the cost, up to $1,000, of qualified intelligent vehicle systems property. Defines &quot;qualified intelligent systems property&quot; as any device installed by a motor vehicle manufacturer to enhance the safety or security of a driver, passenger, or load by, among other things, warning or informing a driver of dangerous driving conditions or by actively monitoring and adjusting driver workload. Terminates the deduction after 2010.</p> <p>Exempts intelligent vehicle systems properties from the first $5,000 of the excise tax on heavy trucks and trailers sold at retail.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
